    for j in i.keys(): #j -  "year", "category", "laureates", "overallMotivation"

                firstnames.append("No")
                surnames.append("laureates")
            if j == 'year':
                years.append(int(i[j]))
            if j == "laureates":
               for k in i[j]: #k -    ( 1-2 ,        )   "laureates" 
                    for d in k: #d -

                            firstnames.append(k[d])
                        if d == "surname":
                            surnames.append(k[d])

def replacer(target_str, to_replace):
    for i, j in to_replace.items():
        target_str = target_str.replace(i, j)
    return target_str
